    "author_channel_id": "UCVJFYJKlCwwsTay3RprF_3A",
    "text": "i have this wonder regarding steam , the thing is, for electromagnets , there's windings and then they're optimized , when i imagine coiling metal tubing around center similar , it'd be easy to measure the output pressure and the steam temperature as it exits , ...in a car the radiator has some pressure but there's no reason it couldn't utilize the pressure and spin a similar hub , probably adding to the cooling effect and it could weigh less than an alternator for example or be used as an alternator drive with no parasitic strain on the motor from a belt [edit: maybe a clutched alternator dive so it switches once hot enough to operate ]....(gears turning is all ...God Bless you, thanks",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2024-10-20T18:49:47Z",
    "reply_count": 0,
    "replies": []
  },
