    "author_channel_id": "UCBUmidh4fkbQzIFdy4yj8Eg",
    "text": "If I understand this correctly I basically need to have the belt before i can cut the disc, am I correct?. Otherwise the point where the belt connects on the disc would be all wonky",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2024-09-21T07:18:02Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgxpCfrTrP9VQpn3G1x4AaABAg.A8dQL9F_tAqA8dTFakIDHS",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "you can have the disk first - just make sure it is around the same width as the belt - cut you belt to roughly the right size then shave little bits off the dusk until the belt fits - the 'wonkyness' at the ends is really abut your workmanship so do it carefully",
        "likes": 0,
        "published_at": "2024-09-21T07:43:30Z"
      }
    ]
  },
