    "author": "@AndrewOudin",
    "author_channel_id": "UC8xRznNoEmibUQvFmXsX4aw",
    "text": "Very nice. Couple years ago I experimented with bonding synthetic rubbers by gluing test patches to the bottom of my shoes with different adhesives. I was frankly astonished by how the cyanoacrylate held up to wear. I expected the glue to become brittle and fail, but the bond outlasted sole rubbers. I have not found that same level of adhesion between sole rubbers and leather, but when I'm gluing eva outsole material to itself I have found nothing superior to ordinary super glue.",
